Results of longitudinal BOLD delay manuscript

Ahmed Khalil

April 16, 2018

This is a comprehensive report of all the results of the Longitudinal BOLD delay manuscript, submitted to JCBFM in April 2018. Code written by Ahmed A Khalil (ahmed-abdelrahim.khalil@charite.de).

NB: These are all the results and plots reported in the manuscript & supplementary material & uploaded to the online repository.

NB: All effect sizes for the Wilcoxon signed-rank test (paired, i.e.two dependent groups) calculated according to Rosenthal, Robert. Parametric measures of effect size. The handbook of research synthesis (1994): 231-244.

2 Volumetric analysis

2.1 Figure 1 - Volume Boxplots with points overlain (manual delineation)

Note that for the first 2 subfigures (A-B), ALL patients in the sample are included. For the last 2 subfigures (C-D), only patients who had both BD and Tmax are included.

2.2 Supp Figure 1 - Volume Boxplots (automated delineation)

Note that for the first 2 subfigures (A-B), ALL patients in the sample are included. For the last subfigure (C), only patients who had both BD and Tmax are included.

2.3 Lesion growth in recanalizers vs non-recanalizers

Difference between DWI lesion growth in recanalizers (median=1.02, IQR=0.962) vs non-recanalizers (median=1.46, IQR=1.132.71), p=0.3501179

Difference between BOLD delay lesion growth (manual) in recanalizers (median=0.195, IQR=0.0550.5975) vs non-recanalizers (median=1.47, IQR=1.221.67), p=0.0015984

Difference between BOLD delay lesion growth (auto) in recanalizers (median=0.37, IQR=0.320.6) vs non-recanalizers (median=1.34, IQR=1.241.38), p=0.0015984

In patients with vessel recanalization within 24 hours of baseline imaging, BOLD delay lesions become smaller. In patients with persistent vessel occlusion (PVO), BOLD delay lesions expand, unlike Tmax lesions, which tend to remain stable/shrink a little in this situation.

2.4 Correlation between volume ratios and TIMI scores

Spearmans rank correlation rho between BOLD delay volume ratio (manual) and TIMI score is -0.72, p = 0.00266.

Spearmans rank correlation rho between BOLD delay volume ratio (auto) and TIMI score is -0.7, p = 0.00372.

The change in BOLD delay lesion volume between baseline (D0) and follow-up (D1) correlates with the degree of vessel recanalization as measured by the TIMI score.
